      "CVE": "CVE-2026-40340",
      "Description": "libgphoto2 is a camera access and control library. Versions up to and including 2.5.33 have an out-of-bounds read vulnerability in `ptp_unpack_OI()` in `camlibs/ptp2/ptp-pack.c` (lines 530-563). The function validates `len \u003c PTP_oi_SequenceNumber` (i.e., len \u003c 48) but subsequently accesses offsets 48-56, up to 9 bytes beyond the validated boundary, via the Samsung Galaxy 64-bit objectsize detection heuristic. Commit 7c7f515bc88c3d0c4098ac965d313518e0ccbe33 fixes the issue.",
